Description: Body sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos or column-krater; interior reserved; exterior, cream slip: band of short tongues between bands above frieze with head of a sphinx to left, facing large plant-ornament; red patches on hair of sphinx and on alternate sections of plant-ornament.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Ashmolean Museum, Oxford. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: CVA Oxford II / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum Great Britain 9 Oxford fasicule 2 (IId pl. IV, 50)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.422)
Previous owner: Currently owned by: Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford
